From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Scott Ames <scottames@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Raise minimum CMake version to 3.5

CMake 4 removes compatibility with projects that declare a policy
version older than 3.5. Fedora 44 ships CMake 4, so cmark-gfm fails to
configure unless the minimum version is raised.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.0)
+cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.5)
 project(cmark-gfm)
 
 set(PROJECT_VERSION_MAJOR 0)
